Exercise
Using a vector of integers, write a loop that prints:

‚ÄúFizz‚Äù if divisible by 3
‚ÄúBuzz‚Äù if divisible by 5
‚ÄúFizzBuzz‚Äù if divisible by both
The number otherwise

Use this vector: vec![1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 15]

Solution


View solution

fn main() {
    let nums = vec![1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 15];

    for n in nums {
        if n % 15 == 0 {
            println!("FizzBuzz");
        } else if n % 3 == 0 {
            println!("Fizz");
        } else if n % 5 == 0 {
            println!("Buzz");
        } else {
            println!("{}", n);
        }
    }
}

Create a vector of 5 or more f64 values (Vec&lt;f64&gt;)
Use a for loop to calculate the mean of the vector
Print the result







Note



We‚Äôve been working only with integers. To create a float (number with decimals) use 0.0 or specify the type manually e.g.¬†0f64.



Solution


View solution

fn main() {
    let x = vec![1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0];

    let n = x.len() as f64;
    let mut total = 0.0;

    for xi in x {
        total += xi;
    }

    println!("The mean is: {}", total / n);
}

